<list id="fs-idm255143472" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic" class="no-style">
<item>What activities make up the strategic management process?</item>
</list>
</note>
<section id="fs-idm237683552" class="section-summary">
<list id="fs-idm248894752" list-type="enumerated">
<item>What is the strategic management process?</item>
</list>
<para id="fs-idm253773968">The strategic management process is the set of activities that firm managers undertake to put their firms in the best possible position to compete successfully in the marketplace. Strategic management is made up of several distinct activities: developing the firm’s vision and mission; strategic analysis; developing objectives; creating, choosing, and implementing strategies; and measuring and evaluating performance.</para>
</section>
